Could you please provide the password to the folder please?

> On 25 Sep 2025, at 1:01=E2=80=AFPM, Privacy <Privacy@tower.co.nz> =
wrote:
>=20
> Kia ora Rafaella,
> =20
> Thank you for your detailed email and for raising these concerns. I =
want to acknowledge the stress and frustration this situation has =
caused, especially given the circumstances you're already navigating =
following the fire. We take your concerns seriously and are committed to =
addressing them thoroughly and respectfully.
> =20
> A) Security / Containment
> We sincerely apologise for the oversight regarding the link access. We =
have now:
> Disabled the current ShareFile link.
> Initiated a reissue of access that is restricted and tied solely to =
your email =
address.https://towernz.sharefile.com/d-sb3797728cdc745088741e36a60cdfbe1
> A full audit log from ShareFile, including activity, and access =
events. This has been uploaded to your file.
> We have used the Privacy Commissioners =E2=80=9CNotifyUs=E2=80=9D tool =
as requested on 15 September to review whether this incident meets the =
threshold for a notifiable privacy breach under the Privacy Act. We =
confirm the outcome of that assessment return being unlikely event, due =
to that Tower can see who has access to the link and the link has only =
been shared to yourself. The report is also included in your file in the =
link.
> =20
> B) Substantive Privacy Act Response
> We acknowledge your original request and the legal entitlements under =
IPP6 of the Privacy Act 2020. We are now conducting a fresh, =
enterprise-wide search across all relevant systems and third-party =
providers to ensure completeness. This includes:
> Internal communications (email, IM, call logs, transcripts)
> Third-party instructions and correspondence
> Site media and technical reports
> ShareFile configuration and access logs. Already included.
> =20
> However, we won=E2=80=99t be providing a document index for this =
privacy request, as creating one would be a significant administrative =
task and isn=E2=80=99t something we=E2=80=99re required to do under the =
Privacy Act. The Act requires us to provide access to existing personal =
information, but not to create new documents or indexes. We=E2=80=99d =
also like to note that if a request is particularly detailed or requires =
a lot of extra work to process, we are entitled to charge a reasonable =
fee to cover the administrative costs involved.
> =20
> Grounds for any redactions or withholdings, however, some documents =
have been withheld or redacted because they contain the personal =
information of other individuals, which we are legally required to =
protect under the Privacy Act. Additionally, certain documents include =
commercially sensitive information=E2=80=94such as contractor pricing or =
internal business processes, that cannot be disclosed. We understand =
this may be disappointing, and we=E2=80=99re committed to being as =
transparent as possible within those legal and commercial boundaries. =
This said, we will provide more detail where we can on the specific =
redactions.
> =20
> C) Records Preservation
> We confirm that all records relating to your claims are being =
preserved until both matters are fully resolved and all requested =
documentation has been provided.
> =20
> We appreciate your patience and your clear articulation of the issues. =
Please know that we are treating this with urgency and care, and we are =
committed to resolving it directly with you.
> =20
> Warm regards
> <image001.png>
> Johann Engelbrecht
> Compliance and Privacy Advisor
> Level 5, 136 Fanshawe Street,
> PO Box 90347, Auckland 1142
> <image002.png>
> Fair Insurance Code
> Tower is a member of the Insurance Council of New Zealand (ICNZ).
> We abide by the ICNZ Fair Insurance Code =
<https://www.icnz.org.nz/fair-insurance-code/>.=20
> =20
> =20
> =20
>=20
> Classification: Sensitive
> From: Raffaella del Prete <raffaellanz@icloud.com =
<mailto:raffaellanz@icloud.com>>
> Sent: Thursday, 18 September 2025 6:42 pm
> To: Privacy <Privacy@tower.co.nz <mailto:Privacy@tower.co.nz>>
> Subject: Re: Privacy Request
> Importance: High
> =20
> Kia ora Privacy Team, Thanks for checking in. I can access the link; =
however, it is not identity-restricted. As a test, I could open the =
folder using a different, unknown email address simply by entering a =
name and passing reCAPTCHA. I=E2=80=99ve saved
> Kia ora Privacy Team,
> =20
> Thanks for checking in. I can access the link; however, it is not =
identity-restricted. As a test, I could open the folder using a =
different, unknown email address simply by entering a name and passing =
reCAPTCHA. I=E2=80=99ve saved screenshots. Please treat this as a =
security issue.
> =20
> For clarity, on 1 July 2025 I requested a full copy of my file for =
both claims (C90306048 and C90306256), =E2=80=9Cincluding all internal =
notes, reports, third-party correspondence, scopes, assessments, emails, =
and any other material Tower holds in relation to these claims.=E2=80=9D
> Legal effect: Under IPP6 Privacy Act 2020, I=E2=80=99m entitled to =
access my personal information. =E2=80=9CIncluding=E2=80=9D is =
non-exhaustive, covering all formats and systems (e.g., email, =
IM/Teams/Slack, call recordings/transcripts, SMS, photos/video, test =
results, and native costing spreadsheets). It also extends to =
information held for Tower by its agents/contractors. If anything is =
withheld or redacted, please identify the specific ground(s).
> =20
> Fair Insurance Code: As a signatory, Tower commits to handling claims =
and complaints honestly, fairly, transparently, and in a timely way, =
with clear communication about what you will do and when. The insecure =
link, incomplete response, and broad redactions to date don=E2=80=99t =
feel consistent with those commitments.
> =20
> I also want to note the human impact. I=E2=80=99m already dealing with =
the aftermath of the fire; the insecure link, incomplete response, and =
redactions have added avoidable stress and time burden.
> =20
> REQUESTS AND TIMEFRAMES
> =20
> A) Security / containment =E2=80=93 by 5:00pm NZT, Thursday 25 =
September 2025
> =20
> Revoke/disable the current link(s) and re-issue recipient-specific =
access tied solely to my email (no public link).
> Provide ShareFile audit logs (link creation, permissions, and all =
access events: timestamp, user/email, IP, action).
> Confirm the containment steps taken and whether a notifiable privacy =
breach assessment was made; if notified, please provide the OPC =
reference number; if not, please provide your serious-harm assessment.
> =20
> B) Substantive Privacy Act response =E2=80=93 by 5:00pm NZT, Thursday =
25 September 2025
> =20
> Please conduct a fresh, enterprise-wide search and provide the =
complete files across all systems and agents/contractors for both =
claims, including (non-exhaustive):
> Claim diary/notes and task logs (full chronology).
> Internal communications: emails and IM (e.g., Teams/Slack).
> Call recordings/transcripts for all calls with me (inbound/outbound), =
any video calls, and voicemail.
> SMS/texts and chat messages with me.
> Instructions to/from assessors and contractors, all =
quotes/scopes/variations, and native costing files/spreadsheets used to =
build any scope/SOW.
> Site media: all photos and videos.
> Testing/technical reports: moisture logs; soot/smoke/odour =
assessments; HVAC/duct contamination; asbestos sampling/clearances; =
electrical, gas, and engineering reports/results.
> Third-party correspondence relating to my claims.
> ShareFile configuration and access/audit logs for links used to =
provide my data.
> =20
> Please also provide a document index (date, author, short description, =
and system/location) so I can verify completeness. For each =
redaction/withholding, identify the specific ground(s).
> To assist completeness, please include a brief search methodology =
(systems searched, date ranges, search terms, and which third parties =
were asked to supply records). If any category does not exist, please =
state that expressly.
> =20
> C) Records preservation (effective immediately)
> =20
> Please preserve all records relating to my claims =E2=80=94 until both =
claims have been fully settled and all requested documentation has been =
provided. This includes contractor files, access logs and backups. =
Kindly confirm  that any automatic deletion settings have been paused =
for the relevant mailboxes, systems and backups.
> =20
> For reference, the current folder contains only six documents (which I =
have consolidated in teh attached file) , which is plainly incomplete =
for a full file response. I=E2=80=99m keen to resolve this directly and =
will review whatever you provide promptly.
> =20
> Ng=C4=81 mihi,
> Raffaella del Prete
> <image003.png>
> <image004.png>
> On 18 Sep 2025, at 3:29=E2=80=AFPM, Privacy <Privacy@tower.co.nz =
<mailto:Privacy@tower.co.nz>> wrote:
> =20
> Kia ora Raffaella,
> We hope your week is going well.
> Just following up to check whether you=E2=80=99ve been able to access =
the link to your privacy request. Please let us know if you=E2=80=99ve =
encountered any issues or need further assistance.
> =20
>=20
>=20
> The information contained in this email message is confidential and =
may be legally privileged. If you are not the intended recipient, please =
note that any use, dissemination, distribution, or reproduction of this =
message in any form whatsoever, is strictly prohibited. If you received =
this email in error, please notify me by return email, delete your copy, =
and accept my apologies for any inconvenience caused. Please note that =
your receipt of this email from a Tower email address does not =
constitute our consent for you to send any other electronic information =
to Tower by return, unless specifically stated otherwise.


